1
00:01:40,560 --> 00:01:45,950
[THE DEVIL BETWEEN US]

2
00:01:45,970 --> 00:01:49,020
[Episode 6]

3
00:01:51,710 --> 00:01:53,509
Is Dr. Zhang Xue in?

4
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:54,800
I'm Zhang Xue.

5
00:01:56,350 --> 00:01:57,120
Hello, Dr. Zhang.

6
00:01:57,120 --> 00:01:57,570
Hello.

7
00:01:57,700 --> 00:01:59,960
I'm a relative of the patient, Xue Jiang.

8
00:02:01,470 --> 00:02:02,510
The case of congenital heart disease

9
00:02:02,510 --> 00:02:03,230
with a lung infection?

10
00:02:03,230 --> 00:02:03,950
Right.

11
00:02:04,550 --> 00:02:05,470
Are you

12
00:02:05,510 --> 00:02:06,350
his father?

13
00:02:06,350 --> 00:02:07,070
I'm not his father.

14
00:02:07,070 --> 00:02:08,039
I'm his uncle.

15
00:02:08,479 --> 00:02:09,419
I've been here a few times,

16
00:02:09,419 --> 00:02:10,479
but we haven't met.

17
00:02:11,910 --> 00:02:13,310
Is something the matter?

18
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:16,070
I wanted to ask about the situation.

19
00:02:16,070 --> 00:02:16,960
Regarding the child,

20
00:02:16,960 --> 00:02:17,520
I see

21
00:02:17,720 --> 00:02:19,790
he's recovering well recently.

22
00:02:21,590 --> 00:02:21,870
Yes.

23
00:02:21,890 --> 00:02:24,290
Does this mean he can be discharged?

24
00:02:24,760 --> 00:02:25,780
He's just improved.

25
00:02:25,780 --> 00:02:28,310
A decision on discharge
hasn't been made yet.

26
00:02:28,840 --> 00:02:31,310
Did you change the treatment plan?

27
00:02:32,320 --> 00:02:33,040
No.

28
00:02:33,060 --> 00:02:35,160
It's been anti-inflammatory
treatment all along.

29
00:02:35,160 --> 00:02:36,150
The treatment hasn't changed.

30
00:02:36,150 --> 00:02:38,950
Then how did he suddenly get better?

31
00:02:39,840 --> 00:02:41,900
His own immunity probably improved.

32
00:02:43,970 --> 00:02:45,770
Isn't improvement a good thing?

33
00:02:46,079 --> 00:02:46,800
It is.

34
00:02:47,200 --> 00:02:47,760
It is.

35
00:02:48,400 --> 00:02:49,280
So,

36
00:02:50,430 --> 00:02:52,470
after this,

37
00:02:52,620 --> 00:02:54,480
judging by the current situation,

38
00:02:54,480 --> 00:02:55,720
is he in the clear?

39
00:02:56,060 --> 00:02:57,460
We certainly

40
00:02:57,480 --> 00:02:59,610
can't make that conclusion right now.

41
00:02:59,890 --> 00:03:02,890
Because his heart
and lung functions are very poor.

42
00:03:03,150 --> 00:03:05,030
We definitely need
to observe him for a while longer.

43
00:03:05,030 --> 00:03:07,230
It's hard to say what will happen later.

44
00:03:08,030 --> 00:03:10,330
So there's still a possibility
of deterioration?

45
00:03:10,330 --> 00:03:11,460
That's very likely.

46
00:03:11,720 --> 00:03:13,110
First of all,

47
00:03:13,290 --> 00:03:15,240
the patient's underlying
condition is poor,

48
00:03:15,240 --> 00:03:15,670
right?

49
00:03:15,690 --> 00:03:16,130
Right.

50
00:03:16,280 --> 00:03:16,910
So,

51
00:03:17,270 --> 00:03:17,870
if

52
00:03:18,120 --> 00:03:20,800
anything goes wrong
or he's not careful,

53
00:03:20,820 --> 00:03:21,730
there is definitely

54
00:03:21,730 --> 00:03:23,990
a risk of the infection worsening again.

55
00:03:24,840 --> 00:03:26,240
If it gets worse again...

56
00:03:28,030 --> 00:03:28,660
I mean if

57
00:03:28,680 --> 00:03:29,810
it gets worse again,

58
00:03:30,520 --> 00:03:31,800
can he survive it?

59
00:03:32,079 --> 00:03:33,030
Or can he

60
00:03:33,610 --> 00:03:35,400
hold on for a long time?

61
00:03:37,860 --> 00:03:39,530
Are you really the child's uncle?

62
00:03:39,530 --> 00:03:40,280
Yes, I am.

63
00:03:41,230 --> 00:03:42,950
Why do I feel like

64
00:03:43,470 --> 00:03:45,360
you don't want the patient to get better?

65
00:03:45,360 --> 00:03:46,030
I do want him to get better.

66
00:03:46,030 --> 00:03:47,560
Of course I do.

67
00:03:47,800 --> 00:03:48,680
I really do.

68
00:03:49,190 --> 00:03:50,920
It's just that he's been sick for years.

69
00:03:50,920 --> 00:03:51,940
The family is anxious,

70
00:03:51,940 --> 00:03:53,340
and the child is pitiful.

71
00:03:53,360 --> 00:03:54,079
My sister

72
00:03:54,250 --> 00:03:56,190
and brother-in-law have a heavy burden.

73
00:03:56,190 --> 00:03:57,030
I came to ask

74
00:03:57,030 --> 00:03:59,079
just to be mentally prepared.

75
00:04:00,320 --> 00:04:01,040
Look,

76
00:04:01,060 --> 00:04:01,840
as doctors,

77
00:04:01,840 --> 00:04:02,900
we will definitely

78
00:04:02,990 --> 00:04:04,830
do our best to help the patient.

79
00:04:04,860 --> 00:04:05,700
Right.

80
00:04:05,910 --> 00:04:07,690
As the child's uncle,

81
00:04:07,800 --> 00:04:09,800
we understand how you feel.

82
00:04:09,880 --> 00:04:10,560
But I think

83
00:04:10,560 --> 00:04:12,280
your priority right now

84
00:04:12,520 --> 00:04:13,520
is to take good care of the child.

85
00:04:13,520 --> 00:04:14,710
Make sure he eats well

86
00:04:14,710 --> 00:04:15,870
to boost his immunity.

87
00:04:15,870 --> 00:04:16,269
Right?

88
00:04:16,269 --> 00:04:16,730
Right.

89
00:04:16,750 --> 00:04:18,170
Don't overthink things for now, okay?

90
00:04:18,170 --> 00:04:18,660
Okay.

91
00:04:22,079 --> 00:04:22,680
I...

92
00:04:23,360 --> 00:04:25,020
I just have one last question.

93
00:04:26,390 --> 00:04:27,390
Hypothetically,

94
00:04:27,650 --> 00:04:30,320
if the illness recurs,

95
00:04:31,260 --> 00:04:33,170
will it be worse than before?

96
00:04:34,390 --> 00:04:36,159
If that really happens,

97
00:04:36,430 --> 00:04:38,360
I will inform the child's parents.

98
00:04:39,480 --> 00:04:40,040
Right.

99
00:04:40,070 --> 00:04:40,590
Right.

100
00:04:40,940 --> 00:04:42,090
I have other work to do.

101
00:04:42,090 --> 00:04:42,920
So...

102
00:04:42,940 --> 00:04:43,470
Okay.

103
00:04:43,720 --> 00:04:44,320
Thank you.

104
00:04:45,290 --> 00:04:45,970
Thanks.

105
00:04:55,430 --> 00:04:55,980
What's wrong?

106
00:04:55,980 --> 00:04:57,240
What's wrong, Mr. Xue?

107
00:04:57,600 --> 00:04:58,530
What's going on?

108
00:04:59,500 --> 00:05:01,160
Is there a misunderstanding?

109
00:05:02,400 --> 00:05:04,330
Cheng, do I have a blood feud with you?

110
00:05:04,330 --> 00:05:05,330
You were cursing my son like that?

111
00:05:05,330 --> 00:05:05,970
No.

112
00:05:05,990 --> 00:05:06,670
I...

113
00:05:06,800 --> 00:05:07,600
I came to find the doctor

114
00:05:07,600 --> 00:05:09,000
to ask about the child's condition.

115
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:09,680
Bullshit!

116
00:05:09,680 --> 00:05:10,600
I heard everything.

117
00:05:10,600 --> 00:05:12,530
You're just after my son's kidney.

118
00:05:13,380 --> 00:05:15,060
You look like an honest man.

119
00:05:15,350 --> 00:05:16,750
Why are you so scheming?

120
00:05:16,770 --> 00:05:17,980
You're truly bad.

121
00:05:24,550 --> 00:05:25,430
I'm sorry.

122
00:05:25,880 --> 00:05:26,600
Sorry for what?

123
00:05:26,600 --> 00:05:27,800
Is sorry useful?

124
00:05:28,040 --> 00:05:29,140
What are you sorry for?

125
00:05:29,140 --> 00:05:30,820
I didn't think that before.

126
00:05:31,120 --> 00:05:33,240
I really didn't think that way.

127
00:05:33,670 --> 00:05:34,990
I just found out too.

128
00:05:36,560 --> 00:05:38,560
Jiang and Jiajia...

129
00:05:39,120 --> 00:05:40,630
Their six HLA points

130
00:05:40,630 --> 00:05:41,870
are a perfect match.

131
00:05:42,070 --> 00:05:43,000
A perfect match.

132
00:05:43,120 --> 00:05:44,270
The probability is very low.

133
00:05:44,270 --> 00:05:45,190
The children are connected by fate.

134
00:05:45,190 --> 00:05:46,040
You're still talking?

135
00:05:46,040 --> 00:05:46,630
Still talking?

136
00:05:46,630 --> 00:05:47,870
Believe it or not, I'll beat you up!

137
00:05:47,870 --> 00:05:48,720
I believe you.

138
00:05:48,840 --> 00:05:49,560
I believe you.

139
00:05:49,560 --> 00:05:50,000
Mr. Xue.

140
00:05:50,000 --> 00:05:50,560
You...

141
00:05:50,680 --> 00:05:52,240
Just beat me.

142
00:05:52,270 --> 00:05:53,150
Just beat me.

143
00:05:54,390 --> 00:05:54,800
Please.

144
00:05:54,800 --> 00:05:55,390
I beg you.

145
00:05:55,390 --> 00:05:56,190
I beg you for one thing.

146
00:05:56,190 --> 00:05:57,310
I beg you for one thing.

147
00:05:57,310 --> 00:05:59,440
Mr. Xue, I'm just asking for one thing.

148
00:06:01,160 --> 00:06:01,750
The child...

149
00:06:01,750 --> 00:06:02,750
I...

150
00:06:02,950 --> 00:06:03,560
I pray...

151
00:06:03,810 --> 00:06:06,470
I pray the child lives
a long life and stays safe.

152
00:06:06,750 --> 00:06:08,520
If Jiang can pull through,

153
00:06:08,780 --> 00:06:10,510
pretend I never said anything.

154
00:06:10,630 --> 00:06:11,630
I said nothing.

155
00:06:11,630 --> 00:06:12,960
Treat me like a bastard.

156
00:06:12,970 --> 00:06:13,880
A bastard!

157
00:06:13,970 --> 00:06:14,970
A bastard.

158
00:06:16,430 --> 00:06:17,430
But if...

159
00:06:19,030 --> 00:06:19,960
just in case...

160
00:06:21,720 --> 00:06:24,720
can you pity me?

161
00:06:25,560 --> 00:06:26,070
Have pity...

162
00:06:26,070 --> 00:06:27,560
have pity on Jiajia, please?

163
00:06:27,560 --> 00:06:29,000
Jiajia is only nine.

164
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:30,240
Jiajia is only nine.

165
00:06:30,240 --> 00:06:30,950
That child...

166
00:06:30,950 --> 00:06:33,390
I'll give you any amount you want.

167
00:06:33,390 --> 00:06:34,480
I'll give you money, okay?

168
00:06:34,480 --> 00:06:36,140
Do you think I need your money?

169
00:06:36,510 --> 00:06:37,870
I don't need your money!

170
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:38,630
Tell me.

171
00:06:38,630 --> 00:06:39,750
To you, is my son

172
00:06:39,750 --> 00:06:41,000
not even a person?

173
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:42,390
Just a kidney?

174
00:06:42,390 --> 00:06:42,800
No.

175
00:06:42,800 --> 00:06:43,870
Your daughter is a person,

176
00:06:43,870 --> 00:06:44,750
but my son isn't,

177
00:06:44,750 --> 00:06:45,350
is that it?

178
00:06:45,750 --> 00:06:46,240
Don't be angry.

179
00:06:46,240 --> 00:06:47,070
Is that right?

180
00:06:47,070 --> 00:06:47,870
Don't be angry.

181
00:06:47,870 --> 00:06:48,310
Hit me.

182
00:06:48,310 --> 00:06:49,720
How can I not be angry?

183
00:06:52,190 --> 00:06:53,380
I'm telling you.

184
00:06:53,480 --> 00:06:55,400
Take your daughter and get lost.

185
00:06:55,720 --> 00:06:57,360
If I find out you're still after my son,

186
00:06:57,360 --> 00:06:58,560
I'll kill you.

187
00:06:58,990 --> 00:06:59,750
Get lost!

188
00:07:00,190 --> 00:07:00,650
Mr. Xue.

189
00:07:00,950 --> 00:07:01,310
Mr. Xue.

190
00:07:01,310 --> 00:07:02,430
Please reconsider.

191
00:07:02,430 --> 00:07:03,310
Reconsider my ass!

192
00:07:03,310 --> 00:07:04,160
Just think about it.

193
00:07:04,160 --> 00:07:05,270
Think about it!

194
00:07:06,540 --> 00:07:07,870
What are you looking at?

195
00:07:25,100 --> 00:07:27,220
Dad, what happened to your face?

196
00:07:28,580 --> 00:07:30,940
I just fell on the stairs.

197
00:07:31,750 --> 00:07:32,670
Does it hurt?

198
00:07:35,130 --> 00:07:35,930
It hurts.

199
00:07:44,640 --> 00:07:47,230
♪ Over the mountain ♪

200
00:07:47,260 --> 00:07:50,670
♪ There is green grass ♪

201
00:07:50,920 --> 00:07:55,750
♪ Little lamb wants to go there ♪

202
00:07:56,600 --> 00:07:59,120
♪ The old antelope said ♪

203
00:07:59,560 --> 00:08:02,240
♪ Don't be afraid ♪

204
00:08:02,830 --> 00:08:08,000
♪ I'll count to three ♪

205
00:08:09,390 --> 00:08:14,750
♪ Little lamb flies ♪

206
00:08:15,360 --> 00:08:19,680
♪ Old antelopes line up in rows ♪

207
00:08:20,500 --> 00:08:22,940
♪ Tranquil valley ♪

208
00:08:23,060 --> 00:08:25,100
♪ Answer me ♪

209
00:08:25,560 --> 00:08:27,800
♪ Where are they? ♪

210
00:08:27,800 --> 00:08:30,000
♪ Where did they go? ♪

211
00:08:57,030 --> 00:08:58,270
The answers were hidden.

212
00:08:58,270 --> 00:08:59,870
Where did you copy this from?

213
00:09:00,810 --> 00:09:02,340
We did it on our own ability.

214
00:09:05,960 --> 00:09:06,150
Fine.

215
00:09:06,150 --> 00:09:06,870
Then tell me,

216
00:09:06,870 --> 00:09:08,130
what is the logic here?

217
00:09:08,390 --> 00:09:09,200
Explain it.

218
00:09:11,400 --> 00:09:12,630
Come on, tell me yours.

219
00:09:12,630 --> 00:09:13,650
How did you solve this?

220
00:09:13,650 --> 00:09:15,310
Why did you write it like this?

221
00:09:18,080 --> 00:09:19,010
I don't know how.

222
00:09:19,270 --> 00:09:20,150
I copied it.

223
00:09:20,150 --> 00:09:21,610
Where did you copy it from?

224
00:09:27,060 --> 00:09:27,630
Let me see it.

225
00:09:27,630 --> 00:09:28,080
Nothing.

226
00:09:28,080 --> 00:09:29,080
Let me take a look.

227
00:09:35,670 --> 00:09:36,600
Who bought this?

228
00:09:37,570 --> 00:09:38,630
Grandpa bought it.

229
00:09:43,800 --> 00:09:45,000
Here, take this page.

230
00:09:45,450 --> 00:09:46,480
Rewrite it.

231
00:09:46,510 --> 00:09:48,770
Finish answering this whole page for me.

232
00:09:50,260 --> 00:09:51,660
Finish this page.

233
00:09:51,930 --> 00:09:52,510
Hurry up.

234
00:09:52,510 --> 00:09:53,710
I'll check it in a bit.

235
00:09:56,280 --> 00:09:57,280
Pick up the pen.

236
00:09:57,960 --> 00:09:58,470
Dad.

237
00:10:01,550 --> 00:10:02,040
What?

238
00:10:02,200 --> 00:10:03,530
Did you buy this for them?

239
00:10:03,530 --> 00:10:04,030
I bought it.

240
00:10:04,030 --> 00:10:05,160
Why did you buy this?

241
00:10:05,400 --> 00:10:07,120
E-learning is popular now.

242
00:10:07,120 --> 00:10:08,150
The school encourages buying these.

243
00:10:08,150 --> 00:10:09,550
Why would the school make you buy this?

244
00:10:09,550 --> 00:10:10,480
To play with?

245
00:10:14,390 --> 00:10:16,630
It's an educational tablet.

246
00:10:16,950 --> 00:10:19,030
Education requires the right methods.

247
00:10:19,030 --> 00:10:21,220
Since when do you know about methods?

248
00:10:22,910 --> 00:10:23,870
Let me tell you.

249
00:10:24,220 --> 00:10:25,030
Recently,

250
00:10:25,050 --> 00:10:27,000
I read some books on parenting.

251
00:10:27,530 --> 00:10:28,960
I'll organize them when I'm free.

252
00:10:28,960 --> 00:10:30,770
I'll teach you personally

253
00:10:30,950 --> 00:10:33,470
and show you what a real pro is.

254
00:10:36,190 --> 00:10:36,670
Here.

255
00:10:36,860 --> 00:10:37,410
Have some grapes.

256
00:10:37,410 --> 00:10:38,940
Did you do something wrong?

257
00:10:39,510 --> 00:10:40,670
Nonsense. I'm such a good person.

258
00:10:40,670 --> 00:10:42,070
Would I do something bad?

259
00:10:42,120 --> 00:10:43,270
You're helping educate the kids,

260
00:10:43,270 --> 00:10:44,240
and washing grapes for me.

261
00:10:44,240 --> 00:10:44,840
You're acting suspicious.

262
00:10:44,840 --> 00:10:46,170
You're never like this.

263
00:10:46,500 --> 00:10:48,300
That's why I call you an ingrate.

264
00:10:48,960 --> 00:10:50,870
I saw how stressed you are at work,

265
00:10:50,870 --> 00:10:52,730
so I wanted to help share the load.

266
00:10:53,320 --> 00:10:53,910
But you turn it around,

267
00:10:53,910 --> 00:10:54,910
making it look like I did something bad.

268
00:10:54,910 --> 00:10:56,970
Is this that police mindset of yours?

269
00:10:58,720 --> 00:11:00,840
The towering image
of your father in your heart...

270
00:11:00,840 --> 00:11:01,220
now...

271
00:11:01,220 --> 00:11:01,620
now...

272
00:11:01,790 --> 00:11:03,150
has...

273
00:11:03,150 --> 00:11:04,210
become this small?

274
00:11:04,420 --> 00:11:06,150
Alright, I misunderstood you.

275
00:11:06,520 --> 00:11:07,760
That's more like it.

276
00:11:08,200 --> 00:11:09,400
Here, have some more.

277
00:11:10,030 --> 00:11:10,790
Actually,

278
00:11:11,110 --> 00:11:13,170
I wanted to ask you about some gossip.

279
00:11:15,840 --> 00:11:17,800
I heard Wang Ping is on drugs too.

280
00:11:18,530 --> 00:11:19,360
Who told you that?

281
00:11:19,360 --> 00:11:21,150
People at the electronics factory said so.

282
00:11:21,150 --> 00:11:21,600
Well...

283
00:11:21,600 --> 00:11:23,270
Nuanfeng County is such a small place.

284
00:11:23,270 --> 00:11:24,120
Good news doesn't travel,

285
00:11:24,120 --> 00:11:26,120
but this kind of thing spreads fast.

286
00:11:26,180 --> 00:11:28,690
Stop listening to their gossip.

287
00:11:29,030 --> 00:11:30,390
Didn't she take it by accident?

288
00:11:30,390 --> 00:11:31,510
She took it by mistake.

289
00:11:31,510 --> 00:11:33,790
She even gave us clues for the case.

290
00:11:34,960 --> 00:11:37,320
Accidental or not, it's still drugs.

291
00:11:39,070 --> 00:11:40,120
Drugs are terrible.

292
00:11:40,120 --> 00:11:41,080
They spread so fast.

293
00:11:41,080 --> 00:11:43,480
It seems like there's another case nearby.

294
00:11:44,460 --> 00:11:45,150
Wait.

295
00:11:45,820 --> 00:11:47,880
Why are you investigating a drug case?

296
00:11:47,880 --> 00:11:49,880
Isn't that for the narcotics squad?

297
00:11:51,510 --> 00:11:52,320
Well.

298
00:11:52,320 --> 00:11:54,240
The narcotics squad has a big case.

299
00:11:54,240 --> 00:11:55,150
They're short-handed.

300
00:11:55,150 --> 00:11:55,510
So we...

301
00:11:55,510 --> 00:11:57,110
We were transferred to help.

302
00:11:57,800 --> 00:12:00,320
They pull you in just because
they're short-handed?

303
00:12:00,320 --> 00:12:00,790
Those...

304
00:12:00,790 --> 00:12:02,750
...drug dealers are all desperadoes.

305
00:12:02,750 --> 00:12:04,350
They kill without blinking.

306
00:12:06,240 --> 00:12:07,160
Why not...

307
00:12:07,600 --> 00:12:09,880
...take leave to look after the kids?

308
00:12:10,710 --> 00:12:12,090
Wouldn't that get you out of this?

309
00:12:12,090 --> 00:12:13,150
Don't tell me what to do.

310
00:12:13,150 --> 00:12:14,870
I fought for this opportunity.

311
00:12:14,870 --> 00:12:15,550
Why would I take leave?

312
00:12:15,550 --> 00:12:16,910
I'm perfectly fine.

313
00:12:18,150 --> 00:12:18,720
Look.

314
00:12:18,720 --> 00:12:20,510
I know you're ambitious.

315
00:12:20,790 --> 00:12:21,960
But you have to think about it.

316
00:12:21,960 --> 00:12:23,550
You have two kids at home.

317
00:12:23,570 --> 00:12:25,300
You work so hard every day.

318
00:12:26,040 --> 00:12:27,770
What if you get injured or disabled?

319
00:12:27,770 --> 00:12:29,030
Or if you sacrifice...

320
00:12:29,390 --> 00:12:30,080
Here we go again.

321
00:12:30,080 --> 00:12:31,480
Or if you become a martyr?

322
00:12:31,690 --> 00:12:32,530
A martyr.

323
00:12:32,560 --> 00:12:33,530
What if?

324
00:12:34,530 --> 00:12:36,320
Who will take care of Ming and Zhi?

325
00:12:36,320 --> 00:12:37,650
I'm already at this age.

326
00:12:37,840 --> 00:12:38,550
Who will run this house?

327
00:12:38,550 --> 00:12:40,120
Why would I become a martyr?

328
00:12:40,120 --> 00:12:41,630
I haven't died all these years.

329
00:12:41,630 --> 00:12:42,320
Why would I now?

330
00:12:42,320 --> 00:12:43,270
I won't die.

331
00:12:43,270 --> 00:12:45,120
I wondered why you
were suddenly so helpful.

332
00:12:45,120 --> 00:12:46,510
Washing grapes for me
and helping with the kids.

333
00:12:46,510 --> 00:12:48,150
I was just making an analogy.

334
00:12:48,180 --> 00:12:49,830
You don't appreciate my kindness.

335
00:12:49,830 --> 00:12:51,090
You're unbelievable.

336
00:12:51,320 --> 00:12:58,160
[MIX CLUB]

337
00:13:24,270 --> 00:13:25,550
If Tang Sile wasn't

338
00:13:25,550 --> 00:13:27,150
coming to the bar that night,

339
00:13:28,870 --> 00:13:30,990
where was he heading?

340
00:13:42,420 --> 00:13:43,750
Was he just passing by?

341
00:13:45,010 --> 00:13:46,200
A coincidence?

342
00:13:58,040 --> 00:13:59,070
I don't think so.

343
00:14:01,280 --> 00:14:02,310
I don't think so.

344
00:14:13,870 --> 00:14:14,960
Jinbao Street.

345
00:14:41,050 --> 00:14:42,380
Stop thinking about it.

346
00:14:43,230 --> 00:14:45,230
Even I don't think about it anymore.

347
00:14:45,390 --> 00:14:46,150
Look at me.

348
00:14:46,390 --> 00:14:47,450
Having one eye left

349
00:14:47,670 --> 00:14:49,030
is better than losing both.

350
00:14:49,030 --> 00:14:50,000
Isn't it?

351
00:14:50,240 --> 00:14:50,920
Right?

352
00:14:52,300 --> 00:14:53,960
It's the same with eating tangerines.

353
00:14:53,960 --> 00:14:54,550
Look.

354
00:14:54,790 --> 00:14:56,320
Eating two segments at once

355
00:14:56,590 --> 00:14:57,850
is too much to swallow.

356
00:14:58,800 --> 00:15:00,000
Eating them one by one

357
00:15:00,130 --> 00:15:00,930
is just right.

358
00:15:05,990 --> 00:15:06,990
Twenty years old.

359
00:15:07,600 --> 00:15:08,480
It's a pity.

360
00:15:16,400 --> 00:15:17,330
Come over here

361
00:15:17,360 --> 00:15:20,110
to the billiards hall
on the second floor above the bar.

362
00:15:20,110 --> 00:15:20,920
Is it urgent?

363
00:15:20,950 --> 00:15:22,880
It takes 40 minutes from downtown.

364
00:15:23,420 --> 00:15:24,820
It's okay. You have time.

365
00:15:24,990 --> 00:15:25,610
Okay.

366
00:15:27,270 --> 00:15:27,890
Got a lead?

367
00:15:30,320 --> 00:15:30,670
Alright.

368
00:15:30,670 --> 00:15:32,160
I won't peel the tangerine for you.

369
00:15:32,160 --> 00:15:33,120
I have to go.

370
00:15:34,240 --> 00:15:34,900
Longzheng.

371
00:15:38,240 --> 00:15:39,070
Hu Wenjing

372
00:15:39,790 --> 00:15:41,550
is a bit aggressive at work,

373
00:15:42,630 --> 00:15:44,640
but regarding your brother's incident,

374
00:15:44,640 --> 00:15:46,640
she really had nothing to do with it.

375
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:48,990
At work,

376
00:15:50,240 --> 00:15:51,650
don't always give her attitude.

377
00:15:51,650 --> 00:15:52,600
It's in the past.

378
00:15:55,710 --> 00:15:56,800
You have to look forward.

379
00:15:56,800 --> 00:15:57,720
Got it, Ke.

380
00:16:29,000 --> 00:16:29,800
You scared me.

381
00:16:30,390 --> 00:16:31,550
It really took you 40 minutes to get here.

382
00:16:31,550 --> 00:16:32,510
I waited for a whole 40 minutes.

383
00:16:32,510 --> 00:16:33,390
I told you.

384
00:16:33,390 --> 00:16:34,120
40 minutes.

385
00:16:34,120 --> 00:16:34,440
What's wrong?

386
00:16:34,440 --> 00:16:35,270
What clue?

387
00:16:35,700 --> 00:16:36,430
You go first.

388
00:16:38,100 --> 00:16:38,960
Start the game.

389
00:16:42,670 --> 00:16:43,270
What do you mean?

390
00:16:43,270 --> 00:16:44,030
There's something wrong with this shop?

391
00:16:44,030 --> 00:16:44,860
There's nothing wrong with this shop.

392
00:16:44,860 --> 00:16:45,740
Just play.

393
00:16:57,320 --> 00:16:59,790
Look down from the glass behind me.

394
00:16:59,790 --> 00:17:01,630
See how many shops you can spot.

395
00:17:17,750 --> 00:17:19,010
A restaurant, a hotel,

396
00:17:19,160 --> 00:17:20,550
a nail salon, a milk tea shop,

397
00:17:20,550 --> 00:17:21,500
and a supermarket.

398
00:17:21,500 --> 00:17:22,060
So?

399
00:17:22,920 --> 00:17:24,550
Among these shops,

400
00:17:24,880 --> 00:17:26,000
which one do you think is suspicious?

401
00:17:26,000 --> 00:17:26,790
Can you tell?

402
00:17:28,590 --> 00:17:29,520
What do you mean?

403
00:17:29,600 --> 00:17:30,300
Your turn.

404
00:17:41,340 --> 00:17:43,110
I've been watching here all day.

405
00:17:43,110 --> 00:17:44,440
There are always people

406
00:17:45,130 --> 00:17:46,730
driving here to buy milk tea.

407
00:17:49,880 --> 00:17:50,720
So what?

408
00:17:51,490 --> 00:17:53,090
Maybe their milk tea is good.

409
00:17:53,550 --> 00:17:55,070
The customers are mostly

410
00:17:55,480 --> 00:17:56,750
older people.

411
00:17:56,770 --> 00:17:57,510
Mostly middle-aged.

412
00:17:57,510 --> 00:17:58,910
Hardly any young people.

413
00:18:00,030 --> 00:18:00,590
Look at

414
00:18:00,590 --> 00:18:01,680
what milk tea

415
00:18:01,680 --> 00:18:03,010
the young people here bought.

416
00:18:03,010 --> 00:18:04,670
It's not from that shop at all.

417
00:18:05,920 --> 00:18:06,720
I just checked.

418
00:18:06,720 --> 00:18:07,810
This milk tea shop

419
00:18:07,830 --> 00:18:09,090
doesn't offer delivery.

420
00:18:09,090 --> 00:18:10,010
Dine-in only.

421
00:18:10,270 --> 00:18:12,310
If their milk tea is really that good,

422
00:18:12,310 --> 00:18:14,710
why wouldn't they want the delivery sales?

423
00:18:15,400 --> 00:18:16,460
Let's take a break.

424
00:18:21,180 --> 00:18:23,010
Actually, it's about Tang Sile.

425
00:18:23,240 --> 00:18:25,130
Actually, for Tang Sile, the bar

426
00:18:25,230 --> 00:18:26,390
and this milk tea shop

427
00:18:26,390 --> 00:18:27,850
are in the same direction.

428
00:18:29,360 --> 00:18:30,600
And Liu Qiang.

429
00:18:30,990 --> 00:18:32,950
Liu Qiang didn't use to go to bars.

430
00:18:33,020 --> 00:18:34,080
Is it possible that

431
00:18:34,160 --> 00:18:35,590
he bought drugs nearby,

432
00:18:35,590 --> 00:18:37,320
didn't want to use them at home,

433
00:18:37,620 --> 00:18:39,660
so he went to this bar to do it?

434
00:18:40,200 --> 00:18:41,200
Is that possible?

435
00:18:58,960 --> 00:19:01,850
You want to buy a cup
of milk tea to check it out,

436
00:19:02,190 --> 00:19:05,390
but you're afraid of being recognized,
so you want me to go?

437
00:19:05,390 --> 00:19:05,760
Smart.

438
00:19:05,760 --> 00:19:06,950
Yes, that's exactly it.

439
00:19:06,950 --> 00:19:08,200
Why didn't you say so earlier?

440
00:19:08,200 --> 00:19:09,400
I'm saying it now.

441
00:19:09,400 --> 00:19:10,460
Finish this round.

442
00:19:11,420 --> 00:19:13,150
We've only got 20 minutes left.

443
00:19:13,520 --> 00:19:14,240
I'll go now.

444
00:19:14,270 --> 00:19:15,800
It's expensive for an hour.

445
00:19:16,840 --> 00:19:18,040
I'm all alone here...

446
00:19:33,170 --> 00:19:33,890
Hello.

447
00:19:34,230 --> 00:19:34,990
Buying milk tea?

448
00:19:34,990 --> 00:19:35,250
Yes.

449
00:19:35,260 --> 00:19:36,460
I'll take two drinks.

450
00:19:39,910 --> 00:19:41,770
Do you have any recommendations?

451
00:19:41,830 --> 00:19:43,290
The original flavor is good.

452
00:19:43,290 --> 00:19:44,510
I'll have an original one.

453
00:19:44,510 --> 00:19:45,370
Anything else?

454
00:19:45,550 --> 00:19:47,510
Business is really good today.

455
00:19:47,760 --> 00:19:49,620
How about I add some new toppings?

456
00:19:49,640 --> 00:19:50,420
One with coconut jelly,

457
00:19:50,420 --> 00:19:51,460
and one with bubbles.

458
00:19:51,460 --> 00:19:52,060
Okay.

459
00:19:52,080 --> 00:19:53,210
I'd like it that way.

460
00:20:04,640 --> 00:20:05,590
I'll also have an order

461
00:20:05,590 --> 00:20:07,480
of this signature fried chicken.

462
00:20:08,410 --> 00:20:09,410
We're out of that.

463
00:20:10,220 --> 00:20:11,620
What about french fries?

464
00:20:12,920 --> 00:20:15,240
Fried food is all sold out today.

465
00:20:15,560 --> 00:20:17,540
Come early tomorrow if you want some.

466
00:20:17,540 --> 00:20:19,070
We have them in the morning.

467
00:20:19,200 --> 00:20:20,400
Your business is so good?

468
00:20:20,400 --> 00:20:21,530
How much is the rent?

469
00:20:22,110 --> 00:20:23,680
I'm just an employee.

470
00:20:23,810 --> 00:20:25,510
You'd have to ask the boss that.

471
00:20:25,510 --> 00:20:27,040
I'm not really sure either.

472
00:20:29,750 --> 00:20:30,270
Why?

473
00:20:30,490 --> 00:20:32,020
You want to open a shop here?

474
00:20:32,400 --> 00:20:32,720
Yes.

475
00:20:32,720 --> 00:20:33,980
I'm thinking about it.

476
00:20:36,200 --> 00:20:37,410
It's nice here.

477
00:20:37,510 --> 00:20:38,750
Lots of young people.

478
00:20:39,990 --> 00:20:40,990
Look over there.

479
00:20:41,010 --> 00:20:43,570
KTVs, bars, pool halls.

480
00:20:44,270 --> 00:20:45,080
We have them all.

481
00:20:45,080 --> 00:20:47,210
Young people are the big spenders now.

482
00:20:49,200 --> 00:20:50,860
When does it usually get busy?

483
00:20:51,030 --> 00:20:53,200
Usually around 7 or 8 PM.

484
00:20:53,230 --> 00:20:55,710
And weekends get really busy.

485
00:20:56,790 --> 00:20:57,720
Here's the receipt.

486
00:20:57,720 --> 00:20:58,550
Do you scan me or do I scan you?

487
00:20:58,550 --> 00:20:59,400
I'll scan you.

488
00:21:01,830 --> 00:21:02,240
Okay.

489
00:21:02,240 --> 00:21:02,960
It went through.

490
00:21:02,960 --> 00:21:03,390
Okay.

491
00:21:03,420 --> 00:21:03,940
Thanks.

492
00:21:03,960 --> 00:21:05,160
Hope to see you again.

493
00:21:25,990 --> 00:21:26,840
Well?

494
00:21:27,780 --> 00:21:29,040
Something is a bit off.

495
00:21:29,750 --> 00:21:31,430
Their menu is very limited.

496
00:21:31,460 --> 00:21:32,280
I chatted with the guy.

497
00:21:32,280 --> 00:21:33,380
He said he's not the boss.

498
00:21:33,380 --> 00:21:34,840
Didn't get much out of him.

499
00:21:36,750 --> 00:21:38,410
Does the shop have a back room?

500
00:21:38,820 --> 00:21:40,070
Yeah. Separated by a curtain.

501
00:21:40,070 --> 00:21:41,790
Did he get the milk tea from the back,

502
00:21:41,790 --> 00:21:42,880
or just from the front?

503
00:21:42,880 --> 00:21:43,880
Right from the front.

504
00:21:43,880 --> 00:21:44,550
Didn't go to the back?

505
00:21:44,550 --> 00:21:45,110
No.

506
00:21:57,090 --> 00:21:57,610
This...

507
00:21:59,000 --> 00:21:59,830
This is way too sweet.

508
00:21:59,830 --> 00:22:00,720
It's cloying.

509
00:22:00,720 --> 00:22:01,850
It tastes terrible.

510
00:22:03,500 --> 00:22:04,630
What is this stuff?

511
00:22:05,030 --> 00:22:06,110
It's bad, isn't it?

512
00:22:07,780 --> 00:22:08,710
That's the problem.

513
00:22:08,710 --> 00:22:10,040
For something this bad,

514
00:22:10,270 --> 00:22:12,240
why do those people drive here to buy it,

515
00:22:12,240 --> 00:22:13,970
getting several cups at a time?

516
00:22:15,920 --> 00:22:16,960
I observed them before.

517
00:22:16,960 --> 00:22:18,470
Don't they have a back room?

518
00:22:18,470 --> 00:22:20,510
Usually for those customers,

519
00:22:21,140 --> 00:22:23,550
the clerk gets it from the back.

520
00:22:26,480 --> 00:22:27,200
I suspect

521
00:22:27,200 --> 00:22:27,790
either

522
00:22:27,790 --> 00:22:29,440
when they come to buy,

523
00:22:29,750 --> 00:22:31,160
they have a referral,

524
00:22:31,250 --> 00:22:32,610
or there's a secret code.

525
00:22:32,610 --> 00:22:33,990
For regular customers like you,

526
00:22:33,990 --> 00:22:35,740
you just get actual milk tea.

527
00:22:42,830 --> 00:22:43,400
It really is bad.

528
00:22:43,400 --> 00:22:44,270
How much per cup?

529
00:22:44,270 --> 00:22:45,100
Ten yuan.

530
00:22:45,130 --> 00:22:46,140
Twenty for two.

531
00:22:46,470 --> 00:22:47,640
That's 20 wasted.

532
00:22:50,270 --> 00:22:51,330
So what's the plan?

533
00:22:51,470 --> 00:22:53,130
Get someone to raid the place?

534
00:22:55,030 --> 00:22:56,480
It's pointless to raid this place now.

535
00:22:56,480 --> 00:22:58,030
The clerk told the truth about one thing.

536
00:22:58,030 --> 00:22:59,030
He's not the boss.

537
00:22:59,310 --> 00:22:59,920
If you

538
00:22:59,920 --> 00:23:01,070
bust the place now,

539
00:23:01,070 --> 00:23:03,480
you'll only end up
with this lousy milk tea.

540
00:23:04,250 --> 00:23:06,230
We need to catch the mastermind.

541
00:23:13,700 --> 00:23:16,260
Could the boss be Ding Lai?

542
00:23:16,510 --> 00:23:17,920
Whether it's Ding Lai or not,

543
00:23:17,920 --> 00:23:19,510
if I were the boss,

544
00:23:19,510 --> 00:23:20,350
I'd definitely find a spot

545
00:23:20,350 --> 00:23:22,100
where I could keep an eye on the shop.

546
00:23:22,100 --> 00:23:23,830
That way, if anything happens,

547
00:23:23,830 --> 00:23:24,880
I'll know immediately

548
00:23:24,880 --> 00:23:26,350
and can make a run for it.

549
00:23:28,680 --> 00:23:30,880
The problem is, there are too many spots

550
00:23:30,920 --> 00:23:32,520
that have a view of this shop.

551
00:23:33,070 --> 00:23:34,750
There must be hundreds
or thousands of them.

552
00:23:34,750 --> 00:23:36,480
Where do we even start looking?

553
00:23:37,510 --> 00:23:38,880
If we do a massive search,

554
00:23:38,880 --> 00:23:40,220
we'll just alert them.

555
00:23:40,250 --> 00:23:43,310
They'll definitely run
as soon as they catch wind of it.

556
00:23:44,750 --> 00:23:46,200
So what should we do now?

557
00:23:48,160 --> 00:23:48,920
Let me think.

558
00:23:54,840 --> 00:23:55,770
The car's there.

559
00:23:59,640 --> 00:24:00,900
Everyone's here then.

560
00:24:00,930 --> 00:24:01,720
This is Mr. Gu.

561
00:24:01,720 --> 00:24:02,370
Liu.

562
00:24:02,590 --> 00:24:03,200
Ms. Zhang.

563
00:24:03,200 --> 00:24:03,800
Ms. Wang.

564
00:24:03,830 --> 00:24:04,550
Ms. Zhao.

565
00:24:04,770 --> 00:24:05,830
Let's get started.

566
00:24:06,000 --> 00:24:08,260
The old buildings you mentioned earlier

567
00:24:08,440 --> 00:24:11,110
are the former staff
housing for the paper mill.

568
00:24:11,180 --> 00:24:13,180
There are 398 households in total.

569
00:24:13,210 --> 00:24:14,690
Building 4, Unit 1.

570
00:24:14,720 --> 00:24:15,830
The curtains are all drawn here.

571
00:24:15,830 --> 00:24:16,810
We can't see anything.

572
00:24:16,810 --> 00:24:17,920
Let's mark it as suspicious.

573
00:24:17,920 --> 00:24:18,790
In the last year,

574
00:24:18,790 --> 00:24:19,830
through my shop,

575
00:24:19,830 --> 00:24:21,270
we've sold about 4 units,

576
00:24:21,510 --> 00:24:22,670
and rented out 6.

577
00:24:22,920 --> 00:24:25,120
Many landlords and tenants
contact each other directly.

578
00:24:25,120 --> 00:24:27,030
Building 5, Room 602.

579
00:24:27,050 --> 00:24:29,620
There are lots of toys on the windowsill.

580
00:24:29,650 --> 00:24:30,920
Let's rule this one out.

581
00:24:30,920 --> 00:24:31,720
The neighborhood committee

582
00:24:31,720 --> 00:24:33,440
just did a census last month.

583
00:24:33,440 --> 00:24:34,790
Ms. Wang, you're so reliable.

584
00:24:34,790 --> 00:24:35,720
Come on, bring it here.

585
00:24:35,720 --> 00:24:36,160
Bring it here.

586
00:24:36,160 --> 00:24:37,620
I know this place too well.

587
00:24:38,110 --> 00:24:39,240
I recognize this family.

588
00:24:39,240 --> 00:24:41,240
The couple are doctors.

589
00:24:41,240 --> 00:24:43,070
They've lived here for many years.

590
00:24:43,070 --> 00:24:44,160
Cross it off.

591
00:24:45,130 --> 00:24:47,000
Building 5, Room 602.

592
00:24:47,030 --> 00:24:48,750
This family put up new paper cutouts.

593
00:24:48,750 --> 00:24:50,160
Doesn't seem like a problem.

594
00:24:50,160 --> 00:24:50,680
This one.

595
00:24:50,680 --> 00:24:51,790
I know this family.

596
00:24:51,790 --> 00:24:53,190
It's my grandson's teacher.

597
00:24:53,190 --> 00:24:53,920
When I go grocery shopping,

598
00:24:53,920 --> 00:24:54,920
I always see them.

599
00:24:54,950 --> 00:24:55,450
So, what do you think?

600
00:24:55,450 --> 00:24:56,480
Are they good?

601
00:24:58,310 --> 00:24:59,130
I'm blown away.

602
00:24:59,130 --> 00:25:00,610
Building 5, Room 701.

603
00:25:00,640 --> 00:25:01,490
Building 5, Room 701.

604
00:25:01,490 --> 00:25:02,140
Upstairs.

605
00:25:02,170 --> 00:25:03,370
Upstairs, next door.

606
00:25:07,920 --> 00:25:08,720
What's wrong?

607
00:25:09,160 --> 00:25:10,030
There's a gap

608
00:25:11,150 --> 00:25:12,080
in the curtains.

609
00:25:12,440 --> 00:25:13,170
That means

610
00:25:13,660 --> 00:25:14,440
I can see him,

611
00:25:14,440 --> 00:25:15,160
and he can see me.

612
00:25:15,160 --> 00:25:16,810
Otherwise, why leave a gap?

613
00:25:17,310 --> 00:25:18,590
Mark down 701.

614
00:25:18,590 --> 00:25:18,920
Okay.

615
00:25:18,920 --> 00:25:20,680
Building 5, 701.

616
00:25:21,470 --> 00:25:22,960
Which ones are suspicious now?

617
00:25:22,960 --> 00:25:25,520
The suspicious one
is Building 4, Unit 1, 304.

618
00:25:26,520 --> 00:25:28,790
-The suspect is Building 5, 701.
-Building 5, 701.

619
00:25:28,790 --> 00:25:29,510
Okay, I'll ask Zhang Yan.

620
00:25:29,510 --> 00:25:31,440
I'll have Zhang Yan check it.

621
00:25:37,440 --> 00:25:37,960
Zhang Yan.

622
00:25:37,960 --> 00:25:40,360
Come to the East Lane
behind Jinbao Street.

623
00:25:42,830 --> 00:25:43,720
Hello, sir.

624
00:25:43,720 --> 00:25:45,970
I'm from
the county public security bureau.

625
00:25:45,970 --> 00:25:47,680
I'm here to ask you a few questions.

626
00:25:47,680 --> 00:25:48,280
What is it?

627
00:25:49,330 --> 00:25:51,270
You're the owner of
Room 701 in Building 5

628
00:25:51,270 --> 00:25:53,000
on East Guangming Lane, right?

629
00:25:53,640 --> 00:25:54,360
Yes.

630
00:25:55,170 --> 00:25:57,060
Do you live in this house now?

631
00:25:57,750 --> 00:25:59,600
No, I rented it out.

632
00:25:59,700 --> 00:26:01,430
How long has it been rented out?

633
00:26:01,570 --> 00:26:02,920
Quite a while.

634
00:26:04,680 --> 00:26:06,540
You know who the tenant is, right?

635
00:26:07,210 --> 00:26:08,650
I saw her ID info.

636
00:26:09,060 --> 00:26:09,830
She's a woman.

637
00:26:09,830 --> 00:26:10,720
In her forties.

638
00:26:11,300 --> 00:26:11,880
This is her.

639
00:26:11,880 --> 00:26:12,540
Take a look.

640
00:26:21,360 --> 00:26:21,710
Sir.

641
00:26:22,200 --> 00:26:22,640
Hello.

642
00:26:23,030 --> 00:26:23,720
Excuse me.

643
00:26:23,920 --> 00:26:24,350
Hello.

644
00:26:24,470 --> 00:26:24,930
Police.

645
00:26:25,680 --> 00:26:27,030
I need to ask you something.

646
00:26:27,030 --> 00:26:28,000
Have you ever delivered to

647
00:26:28,000 --> 00:26:29,240
Room 701, Building 5,

648
00:26:29,240 --> 00:26:30,920
and Room 304, Unit 1,

649
00:26:30,920 --> 00:26:31,680
Building 4?

650
00:26:33,960 --> 00:26:34,830
Let me check.

651
00:26:34,920 --> 00:26:35,350
Okay.

652
00:26:36,680 --> 00:26:37,860
Room 701, Building 5.

653
00:26:37,860 --> 00:26:39,460
Room 304, Unit 1, Building 4.

654
00:26:44,090 --> 00:26:44,640
I've delivered to both.

655
00:26:44,640 --> 00:26:45,440
Both, right?

656
00:26:45,550 --> 00:26:47,030
Do you remember anything?

657
00:26:47,030 --> 00:26:48,960
Like what they looked like?

658
00:26:49,780 --> 00:26:52,540
Room 304, Unit 1, Building 4.

659
00:26:53,480 --> 00:26:55,010
Seems like a live streamer.

660
00:26:55,070 --> 00:26:55,730
A streamer?

661
00:26:55,790 --> 00:26:56,520
A big fat guy.

662
00:26:56,800 --> 00:26:57,730
In his twenties.

663
00:26:57,890 --> 00:26:58,810
Sloppy.

664
00:26:59,030 --> 00:27:00,560
Plays games at home all day.

665
00:27:00,800 --> 00:27:01,950
Every time I deliver water,

666
00:27:01,950 --> 00:27:04,160
he opens the door
and runs back to his computer.

667
00:27:04,160 --> 00:27:06,530
I have to put the bottle
on for him every time.

668
00:27:06,530 --> 00:27:07,870
So I remember him well.

669
00:27:08,790 --> 00:27:09,480
Twenties.

670
00:27:09,480 --> 00:27:10,410
A bit fat, right?

671
00:27:10,670 --> 00:27:11,440
What about the other one?

672
00:27:11,440 --> 00:27:12,310
Room 701?

673
00:27:12,600 --> 00:27:13,800
701.

674
00:27:17,160 --> 00:27:18,160
I don't think I've seen them.

675
00:27:18,160 --> 00:27:18,970
Never seen them?

676
00:27:18,970 --> 00:27:19,920
Didn't you deliver stuff?

677
00:27:19,920 --> 00:27:20,810
You didn't see them?

678
00:27:20,810 --> 00:27:23,070
They always ask me
to leave it at the door.

679
00:27:24,030 --> 00:27:26,400
Do you remember what they ordered?

680
00:27:26,400 --> 00:27:27,330
Any impression?

681
00:27:29,630 --> 00:27:31,300
Just some food and drinks.

682
00:27:31,860 --> 00:27:33,190
Is it all recorded here?

683
00:27:33,280 --> 00:27:34,210
Can I take a look?

684
00:27:34,270 --> 00:27:34,900
Go ahead.

685
00:27:44,220 --> 00:27:45,660
Room 701, Building 5.

686
00:27:45,990 --> 00:27:47,050
Three dozen beers.

687
00:27:47,750 --> 00:27:49,110
A 43-year-old woman living alone

688
00:27:49,110 --> 00:27:50,870
ordered 3 dozen beers for herself?

689
00:27:50,870 --> 00:27:52,590
I'll have someone check it.

690
00:27:57,480 --> 00:27:58,160
Wenjing.

691
00:27:58,420 --> 00:27:59,030
Fengnan.

692
00:27:59,340 --> 00:28:00,400
Check this number.

693
00:28:00,750 --> 00:28:01,550
194...

694
00:28:01,620 --> 00:28:02,340
223...

695
00:28:02,710 --> 00:28:03,640
83765.

696
00:28:07,850 --> 00:28:08,910
Okay, thanks, sir.

697
00:28:09,610 --> 00:28:10,210
By the way,

698
00:28:10,530 --> 00:28:12,160
regarding what we asked today,

699
00:28:12,160 --> 00:28:13,010
don't tell anyone.

700
00:28:13,010 --> 00:28:13,690
Keep it confidential.

701
00:28:13,690 --> 00:28:14,320
Okay?

702
00:28:15,240 --> 00:28:15,790
Got it.

703
00:28:16,200 --> 00:28:17,360
The owner is Sun Wenquan.

704
00:28:17,360 --> 00:28:18,600
Male, 35.

705
00:28:18,640 --> 00:28:21,310
From Hongdao Township,
Nuanhai Town, Nuanhai County.

706
00:28:21,310 --> 00:28:22,510
A true local.

707
00:28:22,510 --> 00:28:23,840
Unemployed, no record.

708
00:28:24,850 --> 00:28:25,610
Okay.

709
00:28:25,840 --> 00:28:26,600
Got it.

710
00:28:27,610 --> 00:28:28,160
Thanks.

711
00:28:30,090 --> 00:28:30,680
What did she say?

712
00:28:30,680 --> 00:28:32,270
The actual tenant

713
00:28:32,270 --> 00:28:33,240
is Sun Wenquan.

714
00:28:33,240 --> 00:28:34,550
35, local.

715
00:28:34,550 --> 00:28:35,560
Unemployed drifter.

716
00:28:35,560 --> 00:28:37,030
He used someone else's ID

717
00:28:37,060 --> 00:28:38,320
to rent the apartment.

718
00:28:38,490 --> 00:28:39,310
Whose ID did he use?

719
00:28:39,310 --> 00:28:41,550
This 43-year-old woman's.

720
00:28:41,750 --> 00:28:44,210
This looks very suspicious
at first glance.

721
00:28:44,710 --> 00:28:45,720
I saw Liu Yi's interrogation report

722
00:28:45,720 --> 00:28:47,440
at the detachment.

723
00:28:47,570 --> 00:28:48,240
Liu Yi confessed

724
00:28:48,240 --> 00:28:50,150
that there is a person in Ding Lai's gang

725
00:28:50,150 --> 00:28:51,480
whose nickname is Quan.

726
00:28:51,960 --> 00:28:52,880
Nicknamed Quan?

727
00:28:52,880 --> 00:28:53,160
Yes.

728
00:28:53,160 --> 00:28:54,440
This guy's name is Sun Wenquan.

729
00:28:54,440 --> 00:28:55,570
Quan is Sun Wenquan?

730
00:28:55,570 --> 00:28:56,400
It's the same person.

731
00:28:56,400 --> 00:28:58,060
No wonder it was hard to find him.

732
00:28:58,060 --> 00:28:59,070
We couldn't find Ding Lai

733
00:28:59,070 --> 00:29:01,070
because Quan hid him.

734
00:29:01,290 --> 00:29:03,750
We can't just go in
and drag him out right now.

735
00:29:04,310 --> 00:29:04,960
Let's do it tomorrow.

736
00:29:04,960 --> 00:29:06,030
Let's report this immediately.

737
00:29:06,030 --> 00:29:07,400
Let Director Dai come tomorrow.

738
00:29:07,400 --> 00:29:07,810
Okay.

739
00:29:07,970 --> 00:29:08,900
You go

740
00:29:09,090 --> 00:29:10,310
and talk to the boss.

741
00:29:10,330 --> 00:29:10,990
I already did.

742
00:29:10,990 --> 00:29:11,660
To keep it confidential?

743
00:29:11,660 --> 00:29:12,470
Yes, I told him.

744
00:29:12,470 --> 00:29:13,270
Let's go then.

745
00:29:23,080 --> 00:29:24,570
I'm just here to see the child.

746
00:29:24,570 --> 00:29:25,790
I'll just see the kid and go.

747
00:29:25,790 --> 00:29:26,480
I just wanted to know where you live.

748
00:29:26,480 --> 00:29:27,940
I'll come visit you often.

749
00:29:39,150 --> 00:29:39,870
Jiajia.

750
00:29:40,270 --> 00:29:40,790
Jiajia.

751
00:29:41,110 --> 00:29:42,200
Daddy's going to take out the trash.

752
00:29:42,200 --> 00:29:43,720
You play with Xiaoyu here.

753
00:29:43,830 --> 00:29:44,890
I'll be right back.

754
00:29:56,310 --> 00:29:56,830
Sorry.

755
00:29:56,830 --> 00:29:57,510
It's okay.

756
00:30:10,470 --> 00:30:11,250
Ken.

757
00:30:11,480 --> 00:30:12,080
Going out?

758
00:30:12,310 --> 00:30:13,290
Just taking a walk.

759
00:30:13,290 --> 00:30:13,840
Keeping busy?

760
00:30:13,840 --> 00:30:14,370
Go ahead.

761
00:31:38,510 --> 00:31:39,310
Come and look.

762
00:31:39,880 --> 00:31:41,230
Does it fit well?

763
00:31:43,490 --> 00:31:44,820
Why are you spacing out?

764
00:31:44,990 --> 00:31:47,790
Your phone keeps ringing,
but you won't answer it.

765
00:31:49,240 --> 00:31:51,240
Is it your ex-husband?

766
00:31:55,070 --> 00:31:56,800
It's my online business group.

767
00:31:57,150 --> 00:31:58,450
There's a gathering in a few days.

768
00:31:58,450 --> 00:31:59,620
They insist that I go.

769
00:31:59,620 --> 00:32:00,730
At a time like this,

770
00:32:00,830 --> 00:32:02,090
I'm in no mood to reply.

771
00:32:02,660 --> 00:32:03,490
Reply.

772
00:32:03,790 --> 00:32:05,050
Just say you're going.

773
00:32:05,570 --> 00:32:06,350
By then,

774
00:32:06,350 --> 00:32:07,910
you might already be at Maide.

775
00:32:07,910 --> 00:32:09,370
You're famous in Nuanhai.

776
00:32:09,490 --> 00:32:11,410
At the party,
even though you won't be there,

777
00:32:11,410 --> 00:32:13,480
everyone will be talking about you.

778
00:32:13,790 --> 00:32:14,880
That's so cool.

779
00:32:20,480 --> 00:32:22,400
Do you have to work with Quan?

780
00:32:22,750 --> 00:32:24,680
Quan has always been a drug dealer.

781
00:32:25,070 --> 00:32:26,480
If the cops find him,

782
00:32:26,810 --> 00:32:28,370
we're done for.

783
00:32:31,480 --> 00:32:32,880
You're scared of everything.

784
00:32:32,880 --> 00:32:34,080
How can we make it big?

785
00:32:35,030 --> 00:32:35,880
Besides,

786
00:32:36,230 --> 00:32:37,160
Quan and I

787
00:32:37,310 --> 00:32:38,840
might not even make a deal.

788
00:32:39,210 --> 00:32:41,100
We'll just run away tonight.

789
00:32:41,890 --> 00:32:43,350
Have you packed your bags?

790
00:32:44,310 --> 00:32:45,230
Not really.

791
00:32:46,250 --> 00:32:48,850
Didn't you say
I didn't need to bring anything?

792
00:32:49,030 --> 00:32:50,830
It's best not to bring anything.

793
00:32:50,960 --> 00:32:52,240
As long as you have money,

794
00:32:52,240 --> 00:32:53,440
you can buy anything.

795
00:32:53,760 --> 00:32:54,480
Here.

796
00:32:54,870 --> 00:32:56,110
I'll send you a location later.

797
00:32:56,110 --> 00:32:57,970
Bring the money and meet me there.

798
00:33:00,070 --> 00:33:00,880
If

799
00:33:01,110 --> 00:33:02,920
I reach a deal with Quan,

800
00:33:03,140 --> 00:33:04,280
I'll call you.

801
00:33:04,920 --> 00:33:06,080
If not,

802
00:33:06,570 --> 00:33:07,630
I'll come find you,

803
00:33:09,270 --> 00:33:11,270
and we'll head straight to the pier.

804
00:33:16,080 --> 00:33:17,120
Aren't you afraid

805
00:33:18,400 --> 00:33:20,000
I'll run away with the money?

806
00:33:24,500 --> 00:33:25,760
This isn't much money.

807
00:33:26,590 --> 00:33:28,650
One full meal versus
a lifetime of full meals.

808
00:33:28,650 --> 00:33:31,250
You can tell the difference,
right, Li Xiaoya?

809
00:33:33,530 --> 00:33:34,480
Of course.

810
00:33:35,350 --> 00:33:36,680
I finally found a chance

811
00:33:37,200 --> 00:33:38,810
to change my destiny.

812
00:33:39,960 --> 00:33:41,920
I'm definitely going to seize it.

813
00:33:42,960 --> 00:33:44,160
I just didn't expect

814
00:33:45,530 --> 00:33:46,930
you to trust me this much.

815
00:33:47,880 --> 00:33:49,720
We're lovebirds sharing the same fate.

816
00:33:49,720 --> 00:33:50,480
If we die,

817
00:33:50,920 --> 00:33:51,990
we die together.

818
00:33:56,160 --> 00:33:56,960
Xiaoya.

819
00:34:01,360 --> 00:34:02,090
Give me a hug.

820
00:34:22,179 --> 00:34:23,060
Good luck.

821
00:34:24,590 --> 00:34:25,550
Good luck to us.

822
00:34:36,840 --> 00:34:37,440
Come on.

823
00:34:37,820 --> 00:34:38,550
Turn around.

824
00:34:43,230 --> 00:34:44,159
What's this for?

825
00:34:44,989 --> 00:34:46,320
If the police catch me,

826
00:34:46,710 --> 00:34:48,110
or if I die in an accident,

827
00:34:48,370 --> 00:34:49,110
the police will also

828
00:34:49,110 --> 00:34:50,710
find you based on this photo.

829
00:34:50,800 --> 00:34:52,330
You won't be able to escape.

830
00:34:55,870 --> 00:34:57,800
You're trying to drag someone down

831
00:34:58,230 --> 00:34:59,670
with you, aren't you?

832
00:34:59,750 --> 00:35:00,750
Isn't that great?

833
00:35:00,940 --> 00:35:02,800
I won't be lonely on the way there.

834
00:35:02,960 --> 00:35:04,440
I don't trust anyone.

835
00:35:04,470 --> 00:35:07,330
Because I've seen
the darkest side of human nature.

836
00:35:07,690 --> 00:35:09,330
If you don't want anything to happen,

837
00:35:09,330 --> 00:35:12,260
take the money
and wait for me at the designated spot.

838
00:35:13,440 --> 00:35:15,570
Pray that everything goes well for me.

839
00:35:15,590 --> 00:35:16,470
When you pray,

840
00:35:19,230 --> 00:35:20,830
be sincere.

841
00:35:21,110 --> 00:35:21,770
Because...

842
00:35:22,950 --> 00:35:24,350
sincerity makes it work.

843
00:35:33,940 --> 00:35:35,440
Why are you just standing there?

844
00:35:35,440 --> 00:35:36,070
Go.

845
00:35:52,510 --> 00:35:53,510
It's nothing.

846
00:35:53,600 --> 00:35:54,480
Sorry.

847
00:37:32,460 --> 00:37:38,490
[Zebin Billiard Room]

848
00:37:46,880 --> 00:37:47,580
Hello.

849
00:37:50,070 --> 00:37:51,880
A bottle of Fenjiu.

850
00:37:52,560 --> 00:37:54,560
Six bags of chicken feet.

851
00:37:56,840 --> 00:37:58,240
Two bags of braised beef.

852
00:37:59,730 --> 00:38:00,330
Okay.

853
00:38:00,660 --> 00:38:01,490
Where to?

854
00:38:04,920 --> 00:38:07,550
Building 5, 701.

855
00:38:12,680 --> 00:38:14,430
The shop is a bit busy right now.

856
00:38:15,800 --> 00:38:17,600
Would you mind waiting a moment?

857
00:38:19,220 --> 00:38:20,350
Leave it at the door?

858
00:38:21,570 --> 00:38:22,420
Sure thing.

859
00:38:24,320 --> 00:38:25,230
701, Building 5.

860
00:38:25,230 --> 00:38:25,840
701?

861
00:38:25,940 --> 00:38:26,530
701.

862
00:38:28,030 --> 00:38:30,360
If you catch the bad guys,
give me a banner.

863
00:38:33,680 --> 00:38:34,340
Hu Wenjing.

864
00:38:34,570 --> 00:38:35,700
We have a situation.

865
00:38:35,760 --> 00:38:36,880
So you're saying,

866
00:38:37,080 --> 00:38:39,480
we have to hit the milk tea shop
and 701 at the same time.

867
00:38:39,480 --> 00:38:40,840
Because they're watching
out for each other.

868
00:38:40,840 --> 00:38:41,800
If one side gets raided,

869
00:38:41,800 --> 00:38:43,000
the other might flee.

870
00:38:43,040 --> 00:38:43,810
I suggest

871
00:38:43,840 --> 00:38:44,610
we take 701 first.

872
00:38:44,610 --> 00:38:46,150
The people in the milk tea shop can't run.

873
00:38:46,150 --> 00:38:47,030
But there's a problem.

874
00:38:47,030 --> 00:38:48,070
The entrance to the 7th-floor unit

875
00:38:48,070 --> 00:38:49,630
is right behind the milk tea shop.

876
00:38:49,630 --> 00:38:50,880
If we make a big scene,

877
00:38:50,880 --> 00:38:52,280
the milk tea shop people
will definitely notice.

878
00:38:52,280 --> 00:38:53,480
We'll spook them.

879
00:38:53,670 --> 00:38:55,590
I mean, I'll take two or three people.

880
00:38:55,590 --> 00:38:56,230
We'll go in batches,

881
00:38:56,230 --> 00:38:57,670
and go up to handle it.

882
00:38:57,850 --> 00:38:58,560
No way.

883
00:38:58,900 --> 00:39:01,200
You don't know
how many people are hiding in 701,

884
00:39:01,200 --> 00:39:02,150
or what weapons they have.

885
00:39:02,150 --> 00:39:03,810
What if there are casualties?

886
00:39:05,070 --> 00:39:06,070
Then don't go.

887
00:39:06,150 --> 00:39:06,960
Let's just not do it.

888
00:39:06,960 --> 00:39:07,480
Let's do nothing.

889
00:39:07,480 --> 00:39:08,440
Just stay here.

890
00:39:09,360 --> 00:39:11,590
When did I say we shouldn't
do it and just stay here?

891
00:39:11,590 --> 00:39:12,590
That's what I'm saying.

892
00:39:12,590 --> 00:39:13,510
There's danger everywhere.

893
00:39:13,510 --> 00:39:15,110
I know what you mean.

894
00:39:15,280 --> 00:39:16,960
I'm asking the city for backup.

895
00:39:16,960 --> 00:39:18,710
I'll get them to come
for a joint operation.

896
00:39:18,710 --> 00:39:20,400
Don't go reporting it all around again.

897
00:39:20,400 --> 00:39:21,550
By the time you're done,

898
00:39:21,550 --> 00:39:22,400
everyone will have fled
and it'll be too late.

899
00:39:22,400 --> 00:39:23,000
It's such a small matter.

900
00:39:23,000 --> 00:39:24,840
Why can't you just make a decision?

901
00:39:24,840 --> 00:39:25,440
Hu Wenjing.

902
00:39:25,440 --> 00:39:27,550
Don't be rash just because
you're eager to take credit.

903
00:39:27,550 --> 00:39:28,030
You know?

904
00:39:28,030 --> 00:39:28,760
Dai.

905
00:39:29,320 --> 00:39:31,190
Do you think I'm eager to take credit?

906
00:39:31,190 --> 00:39:33,630
Don't you know why
I became a police officer?

907
00:39:33,630 --> 00:39:35,320
I admit when I first
became a police officer,

908
00:39:35,320 --> 00:39:37,280
it was just to make a living.

909
00:39:37,630 --> 00:39:38,510
But keeping the peace

910
00:39:38,510 --> 00:39:39,880
has always been my dream.

911
00:39:39,880 --> 00:39:41,380
I know you'll laugh at me for saying this.

912
00:39:41,380 --> 00:39:42,110
But it doesn't matter.

913
00:39:42,110 --> 00:39:43,440
I really mean it.

914
00:39:43,760 --> 00:39:46,220
Ding Lai's case has already
claimed 3 lives.

915
00:39:46,440 --> 00:39:47,230
It's not a small matter.

916
00:39:47,230 --> 00:39:48,550
It's a thorn in my side.

917
00:39:48,550 --> 00:39:50,310
I must catch Ding Lai.

918
00:39:50,330 --> 00:39:52,190
But since there's a chance today,

919
00:39:52,190 --> 00:39:53,030
I'm going today.

920
00:39:53,030 --> 00:39:53,840
I'm going right now.

921
00:39:53,840 --> 00:39:55,110
I won't miss any chance

922
00:39:55,110 --> 00:39:56,000
to catch him.

923
00:39:56,840 --> 00:39:58,840
Can we stop being afraid of trouble?

924
00:40:00,190 --> 00:40:01,360
What am I afraid of?

925
00:40:02,000 --> 00:40:03,190
Tell them to move out.

926
00:40:03,190 --> 00:40:03,860
Right.

927
00:40:15,700 --> 00:40:16,940
You must be Cheng Ken.

928
00:40:18,810 --> 00:40:19,480
I am.

929
00:40:19,840 --> 00:40:20,630
And you are?

930
00:40:20,960 --> 00:40:23,690
We're from the Group
Internal Audit Department.

931
00:40:23,890 --> 00:40:24,370
Hello.

932
00:40:24,400 --> 00:40:25,350
Is something wrong?

933
00:40:25,350 --> 00:40:26,310
Come with us.

934
00:40:28,280 --> 00:40:29,030
Let me finish this.

935
00:40:29,030 --> 00:40:30,030
Give me 2 minutes.

936
00:40:58,900 --> 00:41:04,850
[Next Episode Preview]
